    "Homology is an abstract concept; its general definition is outside the scope of this paper (Carlsson 2009).",
    "In essence, however, the k-th homology (where 0 ≤ k ≤ d) is a group (in the mathematical sense) that characterizes the set of k-dimensional loops in a topological space.",
    "The relationships between the various k-dimensional loops then characterize the holes or voids in the manifold.",
    "When we say there is a 0-dimensional hole, it means that the space has disjoint connected components or isolated points.",
    "In other words, there are no paths connecting certain points in the manifold."
  ],
